> Dear David,
>
> Thank you for your email.
>
> For company renewal, after the first year and in subsequent years, a 
> PMA (Foreign Investment Company) generally does not require a specific 
> renewal process, but it must comply with annual reporting obligations, 
> such as LKPM (Investment Activity Report) submission to BKPM and 
> corporate tax reporting to the tax office. Additionally, licenses such 
> as NIB and business permits should be kept updated if required.
>
> In terms of taxation, both PMA and local PT are subject to the same 
> corporate income tax rates. Employee monthly tax submissions (PPh 21) 
> follow the same regulations for both PMA and local PT, based on the 
> progressive tax rates.
>
> Let me know if you need further clarification. Thank you.
>
> Best regards,
