>         *From:*Nurlia Hasyim <haydenlopez@testdomain.io>
>         <mailto:haydenlopez@testdomain.io>
>         *Sent:* Thursday, 13 March 2025 5:04 PM
>         *To:* SG - David Ling <kellydavis@testcompany.co>
>         <mailto:kellydavis@testcompany.co>; legmorganhill@testdomain.io; SG - Jane Kim
>         <blakelopez@testcompany.co> <mailto:blakelopez@testcompany.co>; Accounts ID
>         <caseylee@mockmail.dev> <mailto:caseylee@mockmail.dev>
>         *Subject:* Re: ALERT: AFLEX: Nominee Shareholder Services
>
>         Dear David,
>
>         A PMA company must have a minimum investment plan of IDR 10
>         billion (excluding land and buildings). However, this does not
>         mean that the company must physically inject this amount into
>         Indonesia. Alternatively, shareholders can sign a capital
>         declaration, stating that their liability is limited to the
>         nominal paid-up capital recorded in the company’s documents.
>         If the paid-up capital has not been fully settled, it will be
>         recorded as shareholders' receivables in the financial statements.
>
>         The conversion to a PMA company will not directly affect the
>         company’s existing bank accounts. However, some banks may
>         require updates to company records, including changes to the
>         Articles of Association and business license status.
>
>         A PMA company can hire both local and foreign employees.
>         However, hiring foreign employees requires obtaining:
>
>          1. RPTKA (Foreign Worker Utilization Plan)
>          2. Work permit (IMTA/Notifikasi)
>
>         Certain positions, particularly in HR, legal, and some
>         administrative roles, may be restricted to Indonesian
>         nationals under labor regulations. While there are no major
>         operational restrictions for distribution/trading activities
>         under a PMA structure, compliance with tax regulations and the
>         Investment Activity Report (LKPM) is required.
>
>         Please let me know if you need further clarification or if
>         you’d like to schedule a discussion to go over these points in
>         more detail.
>
>         Thank you.
