        <p><span style="font-family:&quot;Trebuchet MS&quot;,sans-serif">Thank
            you for your email.</span><o:p></o:p></p>
        <p><span style="font-family:&quot;Trebuchet MS&quot;,sans-serif">For
            company renewal, after the first year and in subsequent
            years, a PMA (Foreign Investment Company) generally does not
            require a specific renewal process, but it must comply with
            annual reporting obligations, such as LKPM (Investment
            Activity Report) submission to BKPM and corporate tax
            reporting to the tax office. Additionally, licenses such as
            NIB and business permits should be kept updated if required.</span><o:p></o:p></p>
        <p><span style="font-family:&quot;Trebuchet MS&quot;,sans-serif">In
            terms of taxation, both PMA and local PT are subject to the
            same corporate income tax rates. Employee monthly tax
            submissions (PPh 21) follow the same regulations for both
            PMA and local PT, based on the progressive tax rates.</span><o:p></o:p></p>
        <p><span style="font-family:&quot;Trebuchet MS&quot;,sans-serif">Let
            me know if you need further clarification. Thank you.</span><o:p></o:p></p>
        <p><o:p> </o:p></p>
        <p><span style="font-family:&quot;Trebuchet MS&quot;,sans-serif">Best
            regards,</span><o:p></o:p></p>
