          <p class="MsoNormal"> <o:p></o:p></p>
          <p><span
              style="font-family:&quot;Trebuchet MS&quot;,sans-serif">Dear
              David,</span><o:p></o:p></p>
          <p><span
              style="font-family:&quot;Trebuchet MS&quot;,sans-serif">The
              conversion process typically takes approximately six
              weeks, depending on the completeness of the required
              documents and approval timelines from the relevant
              authorities.</span><o:p></o:p></p>
          <p><span
              style="font-family:&quot;Trebuchet MS&quot;,sans-serif">The
              company must have at least one Director, one Commissioner,
              and two Shareholders. The shareholders can be either
              individuals or entities. If the shareholders are
              individuals, they may also serve as the Director or
              Commissioner; however, the Director and Commissioner
              cannot be the same person.</span><o:p></o:p></p>
          <p><span
              style="font-family:&quot;Trebuchet MS&quot;,sans-serif">Legally,
              a foreign Director is not required to be physically
              present in Indonesia for the conversion process. However,
              certain procedures, such as bank account setup or specific
              regulatory requirements, may require their presence at a
              later stage.</span><o:p></o:p></p>
          <p><span
              style="font-family:&quot;Trebuchet MS&quot;,sans-serif">For
              the process, we will need copies of the identity documents
              for the new Shareholder, Director, and Commissioner:</span><o:p></o:p></p>
          <ol start="1" type="1">
            <li class="MsoNormal"
style="mso-margin-top-alt:auto;mso-margin-bottom-alt:auto;mso-list:l2 level1 lfo3">
              <span
                style="font-family:&quot;Trebuchet MS&quot;,sans-serif">For
                Indonesian individuals: A copy of their ID Card (KTP)
                and Tax Identification Number (NPWP).</span><o:p></o:p></li>
            <li class="MsoNormal"
style="mso-margin-top-alt:auto;mso-margin-bottom-alt:auto;mso-list:l2 level1 lfo3">
              <span
                style="font-family:&quot;Trebuchet MS&quot;,sans-serif">For
                foreign individuals: A copy of their passport.</span><o:p></o:p></li>
            <li class="MsoNormal"
style="mso-margin-top-alt:auto;mso-margin-bottom-alt:auto;mso-list:l2 level1 lfo3">
              <span
                style="font-family:&quot;Trebuchet MS&quot;,sans-serif">For
                foreign companies: A copy of the company’s Articles of
                Association (AoA) and the Director’s passport.</span><o:p></o:p></li>
            <li class="MsoNormal"
style="mso-margin-top-alt:auto;mso-margin-bottom-alt:auto;mso-list:l2 level1 lfo3">
              <span
                style="font-family:&quot;Trebuchet MS&quot;,sans-serif">For
                Indonesian PT companies: Copies of company documents,
                including the Akta, SK Menteri, NIB, and the Director’s
                ID Card (KTP).</span><o:p></o:p></li>
          </ol>
          <p><span
              style="font-family:&quot;Trebuchet MS&quot;,sans-serif">Additionally,
              we require detailed information about the new Shareholder,
              Director, and Commissioner, including their address, email
              address, and phone number.</span><o:p></o:p></p>
          <p><span
              style="font-family:&quot;Trebuchet MS&quot;,sans-serif">Attached
              is the quotation for the conversion/amendment process for
              your review.</span><o:p></o:p></p>
          <p><span
              style="font-family:&quot;Trebuchet MS&quot;,sans-serif">Please
              let me know if you need further clarification or
              assistance.</span><o:p></o:p></p>
