            <p class="MsoNormal"> <o:p></o:p></p>
            <p><span
                style="font-family:&quot;Trebuchet MS&quot;,sans-serif">Dear
                David,</span><o:p></o:p></p>
            <p><span
                style="font-family:&quot;Trebuchet MS&quot;,sans-serif">A
                PMA company must have a minimum investment plan of IDR
                10 billion (excluding land and buildings). However, this
                does not mean that the company must physically inject
                this amount into Indonesia. Alternatively, shareholders
                can sign a capital declaration, stating that their
                liability is limited to the nominal paid-up capital
                recorded in the company’s documents. If the paid-up
                capital has not been fully settled, it will be recorded
                as shareholders' receivables in the financial
                statements.</span><o:p></o:p></p>
            <p><span
                style="font-family:&quot;Trebuchet MS&quot;,sans-serif">The
                conversion to a PMA company will not directly affect the
                company’s existing bank accounts. However, some banks
                may require updates to company records, including
                changes to the Articles of Association and business
                license status.</span><o:p></o:p></p>
            <p><span
                style="font-family:&quot;Trebuchet MS&quot;,sans-serif">A
                PMA company can hire both local and foreign employees.
                However, hiring foreign employees requires obtaining:</span><o:p></o:p></p>
            <ol start="1" type="1">
              <li class="MsoNormal"
style="mso-margin-top-alt:auto;mso-margin-bottom-alt:auto;mso-list:l5 level1 lfo6">
                <span
style="font-family:&quot;Trebuchet MS&quot;,sans-serif">RPTKA (Foreign
                  Worker Utilization Plan)</span><o:p></o:p></li>
              <li class="MsoNormal"
style="mso-margin-top-alt:auto;mso-margin-bottom-alt:auto;mso-list:l5 level1 lfo6">
                <span
style="font-family:&quot;Trebuchet MS&quot;,sans-serif">Work permit
                  (IMTA/Notifikasi)</span><o:p></o:p></li>
            </ol>
            <p><span
                style="font-family:&quot;Trebuchet MS&quot;,sans-serif">Certain
                positions, particularly in HR, legal, and some
                administrative roles, may be restricted to Indonesian
                nationals under labor regulations. While there are no
                major operational restrictions for distribution/trading
                activities under a PMA structure, compliance with tax
                regulations and the Investment Activity Report (LKPM) is
                required.</span><o:p></o:p></p>
            <p><span
                style="font-family:&quot;Trebuchet MS&quot;,sans-serif">Please
                let me know if you need further clarification or if
                you’d like to schedule a discussion to go over these
                points in more detail.</span><o:p></o:p></p>
            <p><span
                style="font-family:&quot;Trebuchet MS&quot;,sans-serif">Thank
                you.</span><o:p></o:p></p>
            <p><span
                style="font-family:&quot;Trebuchet MS&quot;,sans-serif"><br>
                <br>
                <br>
                <br>
              </span><o:p></o:p></p>
            <p><span
                style="font-family:&quot;Trebuchet MS&quot;,sans-serif">Best
                regards,</span><o:p></o:p></p>
